---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Vital Sign — Body Temperature View
description: number display of body temperature in Celsius degrees (one decimal place)
---

{% from "components/vital-sign-body-temperature-as-celcius-view/macro.njk" import vitalSignBodyTemperatureAsCelciusView %}

<h2>Default</h2>
<p>{{ vitalSignBodyTemperatureAsCelciusView({
  value: "37.0",
  label: "Body temperature"
}) }}</p>

<h2>Elevated</h2>
<p>{{ vitalSignBodyTemperatureAsCelciusView({
  value: "38.9",
  label: "Body temperature (elevated)",
  classes: "elevated"
}) }}</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The unit is wrapped in
  <code>&lt;abbr title="degrees Celsius"&gt;°C&lt;/abbr&gt;</code>
  so screen readers announce "degrees Celsius" instead of the
  Unicode symbol alone.</p>
